For Competitive Programming (Your Goal)
Allocate your study time approximately as follows:
Arrays + Strings (20%): Build a strong foundation. Master sliding window, two pointers, prefix sums, binary search, sorting, and string algorithms.
Hashing + Stack + Queue + Linked List (20%): Focus on data organization, lookup optimization, monotonic stacks, deques, and pointer manipulation.
Trees + BST + Heap + Graph (30%): Spend the largest portion here. Become comfortable with DFS, BFS, shortest paths, spanning trees, tree DP basics, and graph traversal patterns.
Dynamic Programming + Greedy + Backtracking (20%): Learn common DP patterns, greedy proof intuition, recursion trees, and search with pruning.
Trie + Segment Tree + Union Find (10%): These are advanced topics that appear regularly in contests and some interviews, especially in harder problems.
