14. Competitive Programming Tips
You'll learn practical habits that improve contest performance:
Read all problems before coding.
Identify the pattern before choosing a data structure.
Start with brute force, then optimize.
Think about constraints first.
Test edge cases before submitting.
Use STL wisely instead of reinventing common structures.
Learn to recognize recurring patterns across problems.
Upsolve every contest after it ends.
Maintain a notebook of mistakes and new techniques.
Practice consistently rather than solving many problems in one day.
